parameters:
Ramen Shop Owner: "We're closed for today! The oden shop next door
might still be open though."
Matasou: "Haha, Onee-chan has a nice ass, doesn't she?"
Yui: "If you do it again, I'm calling the police!"
Yui: "Really, it was on purpose, wasn't it?!"
Matazou: "Onee-chan's butt is so soft, it's making the old man hard."
Yui: "I told you I'd call the police if you did it again!"

Matazou: "Haha, maybe you actually want to be touched, coming here
like this."
Yui: "There's no way that's the case!!"
Oden Vendor: "Hey, Onee-san, wanna have some oden?"
Oden Vendor: "A set with egg, konnyaku, and daikon for just 500 yen!"
Oden Vendor: "Here you go, eat it while it's hot!"

Yui: (This egg is delicious! The sweet and spicy oden broth has soaked
right into the center, making it a perfect match with the yolk.)

Yui: (The konnyaku is good too! This springy texture is proof of
quality ingredients!)

Yui: (And this daikon! It's been simmered so well that it just melts
in your mouth! The flavor is outstanding!)

Yui: (Wow~! This might be the first time I've had oden this
delicious!)
Yui: "Thank you for the meal~. It was really delicious!"

Oden Vendor: "Glad to hear that! Even though we're in such a dirty
place, make sure to come again!"
Your maximum HP has increased by 100!

Oden Vendor: "Wait... huh? Looks like you don't have any money... Come
back again, okay?"

Oden Vendor: "Is that so, that's a shame... Make sure to come back
again!"
Oden shop owner: "Sorry! We're closed for today."
Oden shop owner: "Come again, will ya?"

Officer: "Hey! A kid like you shouldn't be loitering around in a place
like this!"
Officer: "Honestly, your parents would be in tears!"
Kousuke: "Come on, it's just for a little bit!"

Sana: "This is a love hotel, isn't it... We just started dating today,
isn't it too soon...?"

Kousuke: "We're just going to rest a bit. Look, you must be tired from
all the walking!"

Kousuke: "Hey-hey, won't you go out with me? And then, maybe we can
rest at this hotel?"
Yui: "Haa... What's with you all of a sudden!"
Sana: "Hey, who is that girl! Don't mess around, okay?!"

Sana: "You were buying some weird drugs from a shady guy earlier, and
you've been acting totally strange today!"

Drunk Man: "To hell with medicine... *hic*... after all the hard work
I put in... why did I get fired... *hic*..."
Hiroto: "If you go south from here, you'll hit the soapland district."
Hiroto: "That place was a paradise for men!"

Hiroto: "...or so I'd like to say, but the soapland district has been
demolished."

Hiroto: "It all started when some old guy named Hyetou something-or-
other who had control over the area went missing."

Hiroto: "I think his public face was that of a cult leader of the
Sousei religion... He was pretty shady, so maybe one of his followers
stabbed him."

Hiroto: "Thanks to that, this place has become quite desolate. They
say a movie theater will be built on the vacant lot, but that's still
a long way off."

Touji: "It's great to come out to the pleasure district, but I can't
fully enjoy myself because I'm worried about the car I parked."

Touji: "Hmm, I feel like I might have put on the handbrake, but then
again, maybe I didn't..."
Touji: "Huh? Which parking lot you ask?"

Touji: "It's the one attached to Kokoro Station. I just hope the car
hasn't moved on its own and caused a major accident."
